{
  "_comment": "Cross-SDK parity fixture. Python and JS engines MUST produce byte-identical decimal strings (quantized to 4dp, ROUND_HALF_UP) for every case, or raise for expect_error. Numeric literals in expressions MUST be parsed as exact decimals from their string form (not via binary float). Both core agents load this file; the seed values are authoritative and hand-verified. See REFACTOR_CONTRACT.md §7.",
  "expression_cases": [
    {"name": "linear_input", "expr": "input_tokens * 0.001", "vars": {"input_tokens": 1000}, "expected": "1.0000"},
